# Stage 2: Data Quality (Missing Values)

Missing values were identified not only as NA but also as non-standard representations such as empty strings and text placeholders.

```{r missing-cleaning, echo=TRUE}

## Count missing values 

missing_values <- c("", " ", "NA", "NaN", "null", "NULL")

faltantes <- sapply(vivienda, function(x) {
  x <- as.character(x)
  sum(is.na(x) | trimws(x) %in% missing_values)
})

faltantes

# Count missing values (including non-standard)

missing_values <- c("", " ", "NA", "NaN", "null", "NULL")

faltantes_totales <- sapply(vivienda_clean, function(x) {
  x <- as.character(x)
  sum(is.na(x) | trimws(x) %in% missing_values)
})

faltantes_totales

# Convert non-standard missing values to NA
vivienda_clean <- data.frame(
  lapply(vivienda_clean, function(x) {
    x <- as.character(x)
    x[trimws(x) %in% missing_values] <- NA
    x
  }),
  stringsAsFactors = FALSE
)



sapply(faltantes_totales, class)


```

Results show that most missing values are in *Piso* and *Parqueaderos*.

