# Stage 3: Data Cleaning

## Handling Missing Values in parking (Parqueaderos)

Missing values in the variable *Parqueaderos* are interpreted as absence of parking spaces. Therefore, they are replaced with zero.

```{r replace-na-parking, echo=TRUE}

vivienda_clean$Parqueaderos[is.na(vivienda_clean$Parqueaderos)] <- 0

#vivienda_clean

```

## Handling Missing Values in Floor (Piso)

Missing values in *Piso* are imputed using the median within each zone.  
This approach preserves the dataset size and provides more realistic values than global imputation.


```{r impute-piso, echo=TRUE}

# Ensure Piso is numeric
vivienda_clean$Piso <- as.numeric(vivienda_clean$Piso)

# Impute missing values using median by Zona
vivienda_clean$Piso <- ave(
  vivienda_clean$Piso,
  vivienda_clean$Zona,
  FUN = function(x) {
    if (all(is.na(x))) {
      x
    } else {
      x[is.na(x)] <- median(x, na.rm = TRUE)
      x
    }
  }
)

#vivienda_clean
```

## Remove rows with missing values ONLY for variables with few NA

```{r remove_last_NA, echo=TRUE}

cols_pequenos_na <- c("Zona", "Piso", "Estrato", "Precio", "Area.construida", "Parqueaderos",                                 "Baños", "Habitaciones", "Tipo", "Barrio", "Longitud", "Latitud")

vivienda_clean <- vivienda_clean[
  complete.cases(vivienda_clean[, cols_pequenos_na]),
]

#vivienda_clean

```

